Includes a Land Office warrant, January 29, 1780, to
               George Rogers Clark, granting him 550 acres in Virginia
               for his recruiting efforts. (#6658)

Includes records of the Goose Creek Baptist Church,
               1775-1843, in Upperville and Robert Coombs' declaration
               for a Revolutionary War pension. (#4473)

Letters include anecdotes about the Revolutionary War
               from places the writer visited in North Carolina,
               Tennessee, Georgia and Alabama. (McGregor Library #10547-cg)
